{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πόα</b>, ἡ, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> and <i>Epic dialect</i> <b>ποίη</b>, <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>ποία</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus (see. below), also in 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 333 (trimeter), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 606 (troch.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Boeotian dialect</i> <b>πύας</b>, αο, ὁ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Schwyzer” 485.1, +others (Thespiae, 3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]:— <b>grass,</b> νέμεαι τέρεν᾽ ἄνθεα ποίης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.449; κεκορηότε ποίης, of oxen, 18.372 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν ποίῃ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 368; χθὼν.. φύεν νεοθηλέα π. 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.347; ἀμφὶ δὲ ποίη.. ἀέξετο 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 194, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.53, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] [same place], etc.; π. Μηδική, see at {Μηδικός}. <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> generally, <b>herb,</b> π. τὸ ἀπὸ ῥίζης φυλλοφόρον προϊὸν ἀστέλεχες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 1.3.1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>collective</i>, <b>herbaceous plants,</b> τῆς π. τὸ ἡλιοτρόπιον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 7.3.1 \">Refs</a>]; especially of medicinal <b>herbs,</b> καλοῦσι πόαν ἔνια τῶν φαρμακωδῶν οἱ ῥιζοτόμοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 9.8.1 \">Refs</a>]; of φυλλώδεις δυνάμεις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage]\">Refs</a>]; ποίαν τρίψας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 42(1).122.121 (Epid., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus, see at {ἀβρότονον}, +others \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> <b>lye,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Jer.2.22, “Mal.” 3.2. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>plant</b> in general, π. ἡ βοτάνη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Etymologicum Magnum” 677.49, +others\">Refs</a>]; π. Παρνασίς, i.e. the bay or laurel, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 8.20; στεφάνοισί νιν ποίας ἔρεπτον [prev. work] 4.240: hence, _metaphorically_, κεῖραι μελιαδέα ποίαν [prev. work] 9.37. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>the grass,</b> i.e. <b>a grassy place,</b> πόα καθίζεσθαι <b>grass</b> to sit on, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 229b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 4.1.30, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Agesilaus” 36 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>meadow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Schwyzer [prev. cited] (_plural_). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in later Poets, of Time, <b>hay-harvest,</b> i.e. <b>summer,</b> ἐπ᾽ ἐννέα.. ποίας for nine <b>summers,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Fragmenta” 182; χείματά τε ποίας τε δύω 3rd c.BC: Rhianus Epicus 54; ἢ τρεῖς ἢ πίσυρας ποίας “Anthologia Graeca” 7.731 (1st c.AD: Leonidas Alexandrinus Epigrammaticus), compare 627 (1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Diodorus Epigrammaticus), 6.252 (1st c.AD: Antiphilus Epigrammaticus): in this signification ποιά (oxytone)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] <i>accusative</i> to [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 20, “Etymologicum Magnum” 677.49 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Lithuanian <i>pieva</i> 'meadow'.)","strongNumber":"G8828","accentedUnicode":"πόα","shortDef":"herbage; lye","mediumDef":"herbage; lye","stepGloss":"herbage","stepTransliteration":"poa","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}